  "text": "Let α be a voltage assignment on a graph in a group G, let α be the corresponding lift and let p : α → be the covering projection x g → x. An automorphism A of the graph (regarded throughout as a permutation of the dart set of ) is said to lift to an automorphism A of the graph α if pÃ = Ap, that is, if pÃ(x g ) = A(x) for each dart x of and any element g of the group G. To present conditions for an automorphism to lift we follow the elementary approach of [CITATION_1] . We will say that the voltage assignment α is A-compatible if",
